WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.478 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.478 --> 00:00:27.984 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:27.984 --> 00:00:30.400 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: Many of you
have read articles and seen

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:32.946 align:middle line:10%
programs on how to improve
your brain function,

00:00:32.946 --> 00:00:35.070 align:middle line:10%
particularly now that the
Baby Boomers are starting

00:00:35.070 --> 00:00:37.470 align:middle line:10%
to reach that senior status.

00:00:37.470 --> 00:00:40.900 align:middle line:84%
But what if I were to tell you
that the best path to improving

00:00:40.900 --> 00:00:45.430 align:middle line:84%
this function is through love,
forgiveness, and acceptance?

00:00:45.430 --> 00:00:48.170 align:middle line:84%
What if I were to tell you
that that has been quantifiably

00:00:48.170 --> 00:00:50.120 align:middle line:90%
proven in hard science?

00:00:50.120 --> 00:00:52.010 align:middle line:84%
I'm here with Doctor
James Hardt who

00:00:52.010 --> 00:00:54.160 align:middle line:84%
I went through-- about
a month or two ago went

00:00:54.160 --> 00:00:56.650 align:middle line:84%
through a very intensive
brain training,

00:00:56.650 --> 00:00:59.100 align:middle line:84%
your Biocybernaut
brain training program.

00:00:59.100 --> 00:01:01.020 align:middle line:84%
And I have to say,
it's one of the most--

00:01:01.020 --> 00:01:03.870 align:middle line:84%
if I'd known how intense it
was, I might have chickened out.

00:01:03.870 --> 00:01:07.130 align:middle line:84%
However, it's one of the best
experiences I've ever had.

00:01:07.130 --> 00:01:09.759 align:middle line:84%
So if you don't mind,
let's just-- first of all,

00:01:09.759 --> 00:01:11.300 align:middle line:84%
I want to know about
you, because you

00:01:11.300 --> 00:01:12.400 align:middle line:90%
didn't talk about you.

00:01:12.400 --> 00:01:16.170 align:middle line:84%
We were all there for
a week, 12 hours a day

00:01:16.170 --> 00:01:19.660 align:middle line:84%
with you, doing this
brain training program

00:01:19.660 --> 00:01:22.910 align:middle line:84%
to boost alpha that really
was astounding in terms

00:01:22.910 --> 00:01:24.860 align:middle line:84%
of having to address
everything that

00:01:24.860 --> 00:01:26.670 align:middle line:84%
had been hidden
from our own view.

00:01:26.670 --> 00:01:28.120 align:middle line:84%
And there's no
cheating the system

00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:30.210 align:middle line:84%
in this which is
what's so amazing.

00:01:30.210 --> 00:01:32.330 align:middle line:90%
So welcome, first of all.

00:01:32.330 --> 00:01:34.310 align:middle line:84%
>>JAMES HARDT: Thank
you for inviting me.

00:01:34.310 --> 00:01:36.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And then
also, let's begin with,

00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:37.910 align:middle line:84%
how did this end
up your passion?

00:01:37.910 --> 00:01:39.370 align:middle line:84%
And how did you
go down this road

00:01:39.370 --> 00:01:42.170 align:middle line:84%
to making these
discoveries to begin with?

00:01:42.170 --> 00:01:44.900 align:middle line:10%
>>HARDT: Well, I started
my academic career

00:01:44.900 --> 00:01:46.920 align:middle line:10%
determined to be a physicist.

00:01:46.920 --> 00:01:49.220 align:middle line:10%
I was going to be a
particle physicist.

00:01:49.220 --> 00:01:53.110 align:middle line:10%
And one day, I came out of
the student union on campus

00:01:53.110 --> 00:01:55.920 align:middle line:10%
and there was a beautifully
hand painted sign

00:01:55.920 --> 00:01:58.380 align:middle line:10%
where every letter was a
different color announcing

00:01:58.380 --> 00:02:00.420 align:middle line:10%
that Doctor Joe
Camia would speak

00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:02.350 align:middle line:10%
on brain waves
and consciousness,

00:02:02.350 --> 00:02:04.940 align:middle line:10%
at a time that was just 10
minutes, at a building that

00:02:04.940 --> 00:02:07.560 align:middle line:10%
was right over here, and
I didn't have a class.

00:02:07.560 --> 00:02:10.039 align:middle line:90%
So I went, and I was enthralled.

00:02:10.039 --> 00:02:13.550 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out
he was working out

00:02:13.550 --> 00:02:16.320 align:middle line:84%
of a lab in San Francisco--
University of California, San

00:02:16.320 --> 00:02:16.980 align:middle line:90%
Francisco.

00:02:16.980 --> 00:02:20.340 align:middle line:84%
And he had discovered
a few years earlier

00:02:20.340 --> 00:02:22.970 align:middle line:84%
that brain waves could
be voluntarily controlled

00:02:22.970 --> 00:02:24.060 align:middle line:90%
if people had feedback.

00:02:24.060 --> 00:02:26.680 align:middle line:84%
And he was at the beginning
edges of this research.

00:02:26.680 --> 00:02:28.490 align:middle line:84%
Physics was a
400-year-old science.

00:02:28.490 --> 00:02:29.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, so how
many years ago was this?

00:02:29.740 --> 00:02:31.700 align:middle line:84%
This was like four
decades ago or so, right?

00:02:31.700 --> 00:02:35.420 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well, that summer
after his visit with him,

00:02:35.420 --> 00:02:38.500 align:middle line:84%
I spent every spare hour in
the library reading everything

00:02:38.500 --> 00:02:42.750 align:middle line:84%
I could find about brain waves
three times before I went,

00:02:42.750 --> 00:02:44.440 align:middle line:84%
rode my motorcycle
to San Francisco

00:02:44.440 --> 00:02:46.720 align:middle line:84%
that summer, the
Summer of Love, '68.

00:02:46.720 --> 00:02:47.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, yeah.

00:02:47.580 --> 00:02:51.320 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: And I volunteered as
a research subject in his lab,

00:02:51.320 --> 00:02:54.380 align:middle line:84%
and had three sessions
of about an hour each,

00:02:54.380 --> 00:02:56.840 align:middle line:84%
one electrode at the middle
of the back of my head,

00:02:56.840 --> 00:03:01.020 align:middle line:84%
one speaker giving a sound
from that, and one score.

00:03:01.020 --> 00:03:02.937 align:middle line:84%
And it was fascinating,
and I loved it.

00:03:02.937 --> 00:03:05.270 align:middle line:84%
And so on the fourth day, I
wanted more and I went back,

00:03:05.270 --> 00:03:07.210 align:middle line:84%
but they weren't
doing any studies.

00:03:07.210 --> 00:03:10.460 align:middle line:84%
However, I had learned a
little how the lab worked.

00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:12.850 align:middle line:84%
And I found his
girlfriend and persuaded

00:03:12.850 --> 00:03:17.590 align:middle line:84%
her to put me in the chamber,
put on a few electrodes

00:03:17.590 --> 00:03:19.490 align:middle line:90%
just so I could play.

00:03:19.490 --> 00:03:21.820 align:middle line:84%
Then she went upstairs,
got involved in work.

00:03:21.820 --> 00:03:24.010 align:middle line:84%
Lunchtime came, she
went out to lunch.

00:03:24.010 --> 00:03:27.380 align:middle line:84%
And in course 11 of a
12 course Chinese lunch,

00:03:27.380 --> 00:03:30.010 align:middle line:84%
she went, oh my
gosh, and remembered

00:03:30.010 --> 00:03:31.930 align:middle line:84%
there was somebody
in the chamber.

00:03:31.930 --> 00:03:33.638 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: How long
had you been in there?

00:03:33.638 --> 00:03:34.890 align:middle line:90%
Well, let's see, course 11.

00:03:34.890 --> 00:03:36.920 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well and it
was early morning, too.

00:03:36.920 --> 00:03:39.350 align:middle line:84%
So it went all through the
morning and then lunch.

00:03:39.350 --> 00:03:43.080 align:middle line:84%
And so probably maybe
close to four hours.

00:03:43.080 --> 00:03:44.767 align:middle line:84%
And so they jumped
in the vehicle,

00:03:44.767 --> 00:03:47.100 align:middle line:84%
went hurdling back across
town, raced into the building,

00:03:47.100 --> 00:03:49.130 align:middle line:84%
ripped open the
door, and interrupted

00:03:49.130 --> 00:03:52.760 align:middle line:84%
the latter stages of a
most incredible adventure.

00:03:52.760 --> 00:03:55.930 align:middle line:84%
I had been a Protestant
fundamentalist and a physics

00:03:55.930 --> 00:03:57.480 align:middle line:90%
major when I went in there.

00:03:57.480 --> 00:04:01.708 align:middle line:84%
And what I learned about
the nature of consciousness,

00:04:01.708 --> 00:04:04.120 align:middle line:90%
I was very, very expanded.

00:04:04.120 --> 00:04:06.590 align:middle line:84%
And that fall, at the
end of the summer,

00:04:06.590 --> 00:04:09.740 align:middle line:84%
I rode my motorcycle
back to Pittsburgh

00:04:09.740 --> 00:04:13.790 align:middle line:84%
and registered to be a
grad student in psychology,

00:04:13.790 --> 00:04:17.079 align:middle line:84%
because I realized that this
was going to be my life's work.

00:04:17.079 --> 00:04:19.950 align:middle line:84%
And I needed my rational
mind to be certified,

00:04:19.950 --> 00:04:22.830 align:middle line:84%
stamp of approval PhD
psychology, so people would

00:04:22.830 --> 00:04:25.870 align:middle line:84%
take with some seriousness
the amazing things I

00:04:25.870 --> 00:04:27.337 align:middle line:90%
knew I would be doing.

00:04:27.337 --> 00:04:29.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK now, let's
back up just a little bit.

00:04:29.420 --> 00:04:30.919 align:middle line:84%
First of all, explain
the difference

00:04:30.919 --> 00:04:33.410 align:middle line:84%
to people between biofeedback
and neurofeedback.

00:04:33.410 --> 00:04:35.510 align:middle line:84%
And you had how many
electrodes on your head?

00:04:35.510 --> 00:04:37.690 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well in
that original study,

00:04:37.690 --> 00:04:40.050 align:middle line:84%
there was one active
electrode in the middle

00:04:40.050 --> 00:04:43.912 align:middle line:84%
of the occipital lobe, one
reference electrode on the ear,

00:04:43.912 --> 00:04:45.120 align:middle line:90%
and a ground on the forehead.

00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:46.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because this
was a very beginning.

00:04:46.110 --> 00:04:46.990 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Primitive,
very primitive.

00:04:46.990 --> 00:04:49.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A very
primitive neurofeedback.

00:04:49.120 --> 00:04:52.872 align:middle line:84%
And so just quickly, difference
between bio and neurofeedback.

00:04:52.872 --> 00:04:54.830 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well, it's kind
of like the difference

00:04:54.830 --> 00:04:58.060 align:middle line:84%
between a vehicle
and an automobile.

00:04:58.060 --> 00:05:00.590 align:middle line:84%
An automobile is a vehicle,
but not all vehicles

00:05:00.590 --> 00:05:01.690 align:middle line:90%
are automobiles.

00:05:01.690 --> 00:05:05.650 align:middle line:84%
So biofeedback-- I actually
tend to think of biofeedback as

00:05:05.650 --> 00:05:07.110 align:middle line:90%
from here down.

00:05:07.110 --> 00:05:10.910 align:middle line:84%
Training to warm your hands,
or reduce the muscle tension,

00:05:10.910 --> 00:05:14.160 align:middle line:84%
or change the electrical
conductivity of the skin,

00:05:14.160 --> 00:05:16.200 align:middle line:84%
accelerate or slow
down your heart rate.

00:05:16.200 --> 00:05:19.980 align:middle line:84%
Whereas neurofeedback
is almost exclusively

00:05:19.980 --> 00:05:22.380 align:middle line:84%
from here up, where you're
working with the brain.

00:05:22.380 --> 00:05:25.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And yet you have to
be able to access and utilize

00:05:25.170 --> 00:05:26.555 align:middle line:84%
the mind and the
emotions in both

00:05:26.555 --> 00:05:28.180 align:middle line:84%
to be able to get
the desired effect.

00:05:28.180 --> 00:05:29.480 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Oh yes, yes.

00:05:29.480 --> 00:05:31.480 align:middle line:84%
However, let me
give you an example.

00:05:31.480 --> 00:05:34.490 align:middle line:84%
At one point after this,
I had gone to India

00:05:34.490 --> 00:05:37.710 align:middle line:84%
with a whole range of
technology to study gurus.

00:05:37.710 --> 00:05:40.830 align:middle line:84%
Now one of them was--
one of the devices

00:05:40.830 --> 00:05:45.070 align:middle line:84%
I used-- was a galvanic
skin response meter, kind

00:05:45.070 --> 00:05:47.740 align:middle line:84%
of like the E-meter
they use in Scientology.

00:05:47.740 --> 00:05:53.410 align:middle line:84%
And so I would put these on
yogis, and within five minutes,

00:05:53.410 --> 00:05:55.760 align:middle line:84%
sometimes two
minutes, the E-meter

00:05:55.760 --> 00:05:58.660 align:middle line:84%
would go flat, no
additional information.

00:05:58.660 --> 00:06:01.646 align:middle line:84%
Whereas for an
hour or more, there

00:06:01.646 --> 00:06:03.440 align:middle line:84%
would be continual
deepening, deepening,

00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:04.740 align:middle line:90%
deepening of the brain waves.

00:06:04.740 --> 00:06:08.090 align:middle line:84%
So some of the physiological
parameters are, shall we say,

00:06:08.090 --> 00:06:10.580 align:middle line:84%
relatively superficial
in relationship

00:06:10.580 --> 00:06:12.030 align:middle line:90%
to deep consciousness.

00:06:12.030 --> 00:06:13.770 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so
what was it that

00:06:13.770 --> 00:06:16.600 align:middle line:84%
happened in the chamber that
day when you said they walked in

00:06:16.600 --> 00:06:19.770 align:middle line:84%
on a deeply
life-altering experience?

00:06:19.770 --> 00:06:24.050 align:middle line:84%
And explain the process
of how being hooked up

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:28.340 align:middle line:84%
to this, with the
three basic electrodes,

00:06:28.340 --> 00:06:30.960 align:middle line:84%
interfaces with the shift
in that consciousness?

00:06:30.960 --> 00:06:32.460 align:middle line:84%
So people get kind
of a framework

00:06:32.460 --> 00:06:33.876 align:middle line:84%
that we're going
to be using here.

00:06:33.876 --> 00:06:36.750 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Oh, excellent question.

00:06:36.750 --> 00:06:39.940 align:middle line:84%
The simplest way to
understand biofeedback

00:06:39.940 --> 00:06:41.800 align:middle line:84%
for brain wave feedback--
neurofeedback--

00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:43.420 align:middle line:90%
is to think of it as a mirror.

00:06:43.420 --> 00:06:45.400 align:middle line:84%
If you stand in
front of a mirror,

00:06:45.400 --> 00:06:48.560 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't make you smile,
it doesn't make you frown.

00:06:48.560 --> 00:06:52.790 align:middle line:84%
But if you are going to
be an actress in a play,

00:06:52.790 --> 00:06:54.700 align:middle line:84%
you can stand in
front of the mirror,

00:06:54.700 --> 00:06:57.810 align:middle line:84%
and pull different
muscles in your face,

00:06:57.810 --> 00:06:59.540 align:middle line:90%
and get the feedback.

00:06:59.540 --> 00:07:02.230 align:middle line:84%
So with a little feedback,
you can pretty soon

00:07:02.230 --> 00:07:05.580 align:middle line:84%
make exactly the expression
you need to make for this role.

00:07:05.580 --> 00:07:09.110 align:middle line:84%
In the same way, with brain
wave feedback we pick up

00:07:09.110 --> 00:07:10.910 align:middle line:90%
the brain waves, detect them.

00:07:10.910 --> 00:07:12.080 align:middle line:90%
They're very tiny signals.

00:07:12.080 --> 00:07:14.560 align:middle line:84%
They have to be amplified
about 100,000 times.

00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:17.300 align:middle line:84%
And then we filter
out selected bands,

00:07:17.300 --> 00:07:20.840 align:middle line:84%
in this case alpha from the
theta, the delta, the beta,

00:07:20.840 --> 00:07:22.220 align:middle line:90%
the gamma, and the alpha.

00:07:22.220 --> 00:07:24.380 align:middle line:84%
We just pull out
the alpha and use

00:07:24.380 --> 00:07:27.300 align:middle line:84%
that to run sounds,
musical sounds.

00:07:27.300 --> 00:07:30.310 align:middle line:84%
So if alpha gets bigger
at this point of the head,

00:07:30.310 --> 00:07:32.079 align:middle line:90%
there's a tone that gets louder.

00:07:32.079 --> 00:07:34.370 align:middle line:84%
Similarly, if it gets bigger
at this point of the head,

00:07:34.370 --> 00:07:37.020 align:middle line:84%
there's a different pitched
tone from a different speaker

00:07:37.020 --> 00:07:37.950 align:middle line:90%
that gets louder.

00:07:37.950 --> 00:07:40.730 align:middle line:84%
So you literally have
a mirror for your mind,

00:07:40.730 --> 00:07:42.869 align:middle line:84%
but it's a mirror that
works primarily with sound.

00:07:42.869 --> 00:07:44.535 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it's
working mostly though

00:07:44.535 --> 00:07:46.920 align:middle line:84%
with the subconscious
mind, right?

00:07:46.920 --> 00:07:48.320 align:middle line:90%
Is that fair to say?

00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:50.250 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well, the
whole point of this

00:07:50.250 --> 00:07:52.730 align:middle line:84%
is to take that which
is in the unconscious

00:07:52.730 --> 00:07:54.316 align:middle line:84%
and bring it into
the consciousness.

00:07:54.316 --> 00:07:56.440 align:middle line:84%
Now, for part of that we
have the computerized mood

00:07:56.440 --> 00:07:57.657 align:middle line:90%
scales that you know about.

00:07:57.657 --> 00:07:58.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:07:58.240 --> 00:08:00.340 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Where the
computer can actually

00:08:00.340 --> 00:08:04.430 align:middle line:84%
read emotions-- the
existence of emotions,

00:08:04.430 --> 00:08:07.880 align:middle line:84%
positive and negative, that
the person's unconscious of.

00:08:07.880 --> 00:08:09.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're going to
get into the exact what

00:08:09.880 --> 00:08:12.670 align:middle line:84%
happens in that training
in a little bit.

00:08:12.670 --> 00:08:16.060 align:middle line:84%
I want to warm everybody up
to the notion of why we're

00:08:16.060 --> 00:08:19.700 align:middle line:84%
working with certain brain
frequencies and the basics

00:08:19.700 --> 00:08:22.220 align:middle line:84%
as you just explained
of neurofeedback itself,

00:08:22.220 --> 00:08:24.650 align:middle line:84%
because you're able
to hear in this case--

00:08:24.650 --> 00:08:27.540 align:middle line:84%
in some systems you'll
actually use little earbuds.

00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:29.860 align:middle line:84%
In this case, with
Biocybernaut, you're

00:08:29.860 --> 00:08:33.189 align:middle line:84%
in a chamber where the sound is
being projected all around you.

00:08:33.189 --> 00:08:35.730 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: So you actually feel
it through your body as well as

00:08:35.730 --> 00:08:36.510 align:middle line:90%
just your ears.

00:08:36.510 --> 00:08:38.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, and it
is very interesting.

00:08:38.870 --> 00:08:41.280 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well and to go back
to your question about what

00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:45.170 align:middle line:84%
was going on for me in
Joe Camia's chamber,

00:08:45.170 --> 00:08:49.810 align:middle line:84%
the first four days-- which were
incredibly intriguing for me--

00:08:49.810 --> 00:08:51.720 align:middle line:84%
I'd be sitting there in
the dark with my eyes

00:08:51.720 --> 00:08:55.130 align:middle line:84%
closed, and the
tones would surge.

00:08:55.130 --> 00:08:56.890 align:middle line:84%
The tone would surge,
it would get louder.

00:08:56.890 --> 00:09:00.460 align:middle line:84%
Well immediately, my rational
mind would what did you do?

00:09:00.460 --> 00:09:01.340 align:middle line:90%
How did you do that?

00:09:01.340 --> 00:09:03.140 align:middle line:84%
And of course, that
would make it go away.

00:09:03.140 --> 00:09:05.710 align:middle line:84%
And so with some
practice, what I learned

00:09:05.710 --> 00:09:07.430 align:middle line:84%
to do when the
tone would surge is

00:09:07.430 --> 00:09:10.839 align:middle line:84%
to restrain my rational
analytical mind

00:09:10.839 --> 00:09:12.380 align:middle line:84%
from coming in and
messing things up.

00:09:12.380 --> 00:09:14.560 align:middle line:84%
But maybe I could only
restrain it for a half

00:09:14.560 --> 00:09:16.950 align:middle line:84%
a second, with a little
practice, three quarters

00:09:16.950 --> 00:09:19.280 align:middle line:84%
of a second, with
practice, two seconds.

00:09:19.280 --> 00:09:22.640 align:middle line:84%
But that additional time
allowed the alpha to emerge.

00:09:22.640 --> 00:09:25.460 align:middle line:84%
And that began to
produce a feeling

00:09:25.460 --> 00:09:27.180 align:middle line:84%
