00:20:27.730 --> 00:20:28.460 align:middle line:90%
in at that point.

00:20:28.460 --> 00:20:28.890 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Right on.

00:20:28.890 --> 00:20:30.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, OK good.

00:20:30.120 --> 00:20:32.540 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Because if
you have a big meal,

00:20:32.540 --> 00:20:33.920 align:middle line:90%
several things happen.

00:20:33.920 --> 00:20:37.010 align:middle line:84%
When you eat a big meal,
or really any meal,

00:20:37.010 --> 00:20:40.140 align:middle line:84%
your body temperature has to go
up in order to digest the meal.

00:20:40.140 --> 00:20:42.740 align:middle line:84%
That's why you eat a meal,
and even if it's a cold meal

00:20:42.740 --> 00:20:44.831 align:middle line:90%
you suddenly feel warm.

00:20:44.831 --> 00:20:46.830 align:middle line:84%
The other thing is that
in order to fall asleep,

00:20:46.830 --> 00:20:48.647 align:middle line:84%
your body temperature
needs to drop.

00:20:48.647 --> 00:20:50.480 align:middle line:84%
So if you eat a big
meal and then go to bed,

00:20:50.480 --> 00:20:52.944 align:middle line:84%
you set up a war in your
body, where one part

00:20:52.944 --> 00:20:54.610 align:middle line:84%
is trying to make the
temperature go up,

00:20:54.610 --> 00:20:56.568 align:middle line:84%
another trying to make
the temperature go down.

00:20:56.568 --> 00:20:58.980 align:middle line:84%
You get maldigestion,
putrifaction in the gut,

00:20:58.980 --> 00:21:01.980 align:middle line:84%
and shallow, dream-filled,
restless sleep.

00:21:01.980 --> 00:21:03.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That is very
useful information.

00:21:03.760 --> 00:21:06.480 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

