the audio feedback stops
and for eight seconds

00:27:16.730 --> 00:27:19.657 align:middle line:84%
they get to look at scores that
quantify the power that they

00:27:19.657 --> 00:27:21.490 align:middle line:84%
put out at different
regions of their brain.

00:27:21.490 --> 00:27:23.330 align:middle line:84%
As well as the degree
to which their left

00:27:23.330 --> 00:27:25.121 align:middle line:84%
and their right brain
are working together.

00:27:25.121 --> 00:27:27.090 align:middle line:90%
We call that hemicoherence.

00:27:27.090 --> 00:27:30.470 align:middle line:84%
And so after that
initial demonstration,

00:27:30.470 --> 00:27:32.300 align:middle line:84%
then we go, we
measure their heads.

00:27:32.300 --> 00:27:34.190 align:middle line:84%
A technician puts
the electrodes on,

00:27:34.190 --> 00:27:36.070 align:middle line:84%
and we give them a
PowerPoint presentation

00:27:36.070 --> 00:27:39.745 align:middle line:84%
to give them a little idea
about how this is going to work.

00:27:39.745 --> 00:27:41.870 align:middle line:84%
And then they go off to
the chambers and they play.

00:27:41.870 --> 00:27:45.110 align:middle line:84%
Now, at the end of the chamber
time, we gather in a room

00:27:45.110 --> 00:27:48.410 align:middle line:84%
where we have canopy beds
where people can sit or lie.

00:27:48.410 --> 00:27:50.820 align:middle line:84%
And each person in
turn is carefully

00:27:50.820 --> 00:27:53.310 align:middle line:84%
interviewed to talk
about their experiences.

00:27:53.310 --> 00:27:56.320 align:middle line:84%
When an astronaut comes
back from a space mission,

00:27:56.320 --> 00:27:59.070 align:middle line:90%
they're debriefed, interviewed.

00:27:59.070 --> 00:28:02.100 align:middle line:84%
And so when the Biocybernauts
come back from an inner space

00:28:02.100 --> 00:28:03.930 align:middle line:90%
mission, we debrief them.

00:28:03.930 --> 00:28:06.150 align:middle line:90%
And so that does several things.

00:28:06.150 --> 00:28:08.620 align:middle line:84%
One, it helps the other
people in the group

00:28:08.620 --> 00:28:11.100 align:middle line:90%
to get ideas of things to try.

00:28:11.100 --> 00:28:13.574 align:middle line:84%
And it also helps
their experience

00:28:13.574 --> 00:28:15.240 align:middle line:84%
to be transferred
from short term memory

00:28:15.240 --> 00:28:17.570 align:middle line:84%
to long term memory, so
they'll have a chance

00:28:17.570 --> 00:28:19.006 align:middle line:90%
to maybe do better.

00:28:19.006 --> 00:28:20.380 align:middle line:84%
Or if there were
things that they

00:28:20.380 --> 00:28:21.945 align:middle line:84%
were doing that
are non-productive,

00:28:21.945 --> 00:28:23.820 align:middle line:84%
they could be labeled
as that by the trainer.

00:28:23.820 --> 00:28:25.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or they're
just doing something

00:28:25.470 --> 00:28:27.594 align:middle line:84%
that would be called a
shortcut or cheating, like I

00:28:27.594 --> 00:28:28.830 align:middle line:90%
did the first day.

00:28:28.830 --> 00:28:31.160 align:middle line:90%
I thought, wow, look at that.

00:28:31.160 --> 00:28:32.315 align:middle line:90%
Look at those numbers.

00:28:32.315 --> 00:28:33.015 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Opening your eyes?

00:28:33.015 --> 00:28:33.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I
opened my eyes, but no.

00:28:33.570 --> 00:28:36.320 align:middle line:84%
I was rolling them up
in the top of my head.

00:28:36.320 --> 00:28:38.920 align:middle line:84%
I was rolling my eyes up
and the numbers were going.

00:28:38.920 --> 00:28:41.980 align:middle line:84%
But also when I meditate
and go to certain levels,

00:28:41.980 --> 00:28:43.490 align:middle line:90%
that is what I do.

00:28:43.490 --> 00:28:45.690 align:middle line:84%
But you're not to do that
in the brain training,

00:28:45.690 --> 00:28:49.530 align:middle line:84%
because it's really much more--
the protocols are much more

00:28:49.530 --> 00:28:52.401 align:middle line:84%
systematic than just going off
on your own like I was doing.

00:28:52.401 --> 00:28:54.400 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: You want to learn
how to do it directly

00:28:54.400 --> 00:28:56.840 align:middle line:84%
from the brain without
influence of muscles.

00:28:56.840 --> 00:28:57.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:28:57.590 --> 00:28:59.830 align:middle line:90%
And so, go ahead, sorry.

00:28:59.830 --> 00:29:00.990 align:middle line:90%
So from there.

00:29:00.990 --> 00:29:04.197 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well, so this
is now bringing people

00:29:04.197 --> 00:29:06.030 align:middle line:84%
to the point where
they've had their chamber

00:29:06.030 --> 00:29:07.340 align:middle line:90%
experience for the day.

00:29:07.340 --> 00:29:09.980 align:middle line:10%
They've been to the
canopy room to debrief.

00:29:09.980 --> 00:29:11.830 align:middle line:10%
And then they go off
to the dining room,

00:29:11.830 --> 00:29:13.890 align:middle line:10%
where they have the
meal that they selected

00:29:13.890 --> 00:29:16.990 align:middle line:10%
from a menu earlier in the
day, soup and salad primarily.

00:29:16.990 --> 00:29:20.110 align:middle line:84%
And after that, we go back
to the conference room.

00:29:20.110 --> 00:29:23.480 align:middle line:84%
And we then come out of
the participant role.

00:29:23.480 --> 00:29:25.440 align:middle line:84%
And we bring them
in as like sort

00:29:25.440 --> 00:29:27.590 align:middle line:84%
of collaborative
scientists, where

00:29:27.590 --> 00:29:30.360 align:middle line:84%
they get to study their
brain waves with us

00:29:30.360 --> 00:29:32.290 align:middle line:90%
and we go over the results.

00:29:32.290 --> 00:29:34.830 align:middle line:84%
So you have time to be
the participant as well

00:29:34.830 --> 00:29:36.550 align:middle line:90%
as the observer.

00:29:36.550 --> 00:29:39.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And when you're
in the chamber itself,

00:29:39.220 --> 00:29:41.930 align:middle line:84%
I mean it's really--
it's quite a process,

00:29:41.930 --> 00:29:45.890 align:middle line:84%
because you have to go
through various exercises.

00:29:45.890 --> 00:29:46.870 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Baselines.

00:29:46.870 --> 00:29:48.453 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You have
baselines while you

00:29:48.453 --> 00:29:49.590 align:middle line:90%
have the electrodes on.

00:29:49.590 --> 00:29:50.774 align:middle line:90%
And these mood scales.

00:29:50.774 --> 00:29:52.440 align:middle line:84%
So now this is
interesting, because this

00:29:52.440 --> 00:29:55.510 align:middle line:84%
is where we start accessing
subconscious emotions.

00:29:55.510 --> 00:29:58.700 align:middle line:84%
And it seems like some of
the words that are put up,

00:29:58.700 --> 00:30:02.676 align:middle line:84%
you just react to the words
on a scale of one to four,

00:30:02.676 --> 00:30:07.290 align:middle line:84%
or A to D, and then A or
B, and then yes or no.

00:30:07.290 --> 00:30:09.000 align:middle line:84%
And so you have to
keep refining it,

00:30:09.000 --> 00:30:10.770 align:middle line:84%
right, as we go through
these mood scales,

00:30:10.770 --> 00:30:13.080 align:middle line:90%
passing through these words.

00:30:13.080 --> 00:30:15.670 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: How do you feel
right now, in the morning

00:30:15.670 --> 00:30:18.640 align:middle line:84%
or after the alpha
training while you're still

00:30:18.640 --> 00:30:19.440 align:middle line:90%
in the chamber?

00:30:19.440 --> 00:30:21.070 align:middle line:84%
You do a second
set of mood scales

00:30:21.070 --> 00:30:23.330 align:middle line:84%
where you answer
the question, how

00:30:23.330 --> 00:30:25.470 align:middle line:84%
did I feel in the
moments of highest alpha.

00:30:25.470 --> 00:30:26.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:30:26.410 --> 00:30:28.750 align:middle line:84%
And that is interesting,
because that's

00:30:28.750 --> 00:30:31.890 align:middle line:84%
where the subconscious
information starts emerging.

00:30:31.890 --> 00:30:36.150 align:middle line:84%
And where people start having a
real disconnect with what they

00:30:36.150 --> 00:30:40.355 align:middle line:84%
think they're feeling versus
what's actually going on.

00:30:40.355 --> 00:30:41.980 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk about
that a little bit,

00:30:41.980 --> 00:30:44.390 align:middle line:84%
because somewhere in
there is the message

00:30:44.390 --> 00:30:46.686 align:middle line:90%
of the hidden trauma.

00:30:46.686 --> 00:30:48.310 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well, and
before we get there,

00:30:48.310 --> 00:30:50.760 align:middle line:84%
there's a more
shall we say direct,

00:30:50.760 --> 00:30:53.830 align:middle line:84%
or easy to access use
of the mood scales.

00:30:53.830 --> 00:30:56.130 align:middle line:84%
Because they're
scored by computer,

00:30:56.130 --> 00:30:58.050 align:middle line:90%
and so people can see.

00:30:58.050 --> 00:30:59.850 align:middle line:90%
We give them printouts.

00:30:59.850 --> 00:31:02.210 align:middle line:84%
They can see what their
anxiety, hostility, depression

00:31:02.210 --> 00:31:04.830 align:middle line:90%
level was before and then after.

00:31:04.830 --> 00:31:09.140 align:middle line:84%
And people who have lived for
years in a state of paralyzing

00:31:09.140 --> 00:31:12.520 align:middle line:84%
anxiety or deep
depression all of a sudden

00:31:12.520 --> 00:31:13.720 align:middle line:90%
can see their numbers.

00:31:13.720 --> 00:31:16.410 align:middle line:84%
Oh my God, my depression
dropped by half.

00:31:16.410 --> 00:31:21.070 align:middle line:84%
Or my anxiety went down to a
third in just the first day.

00:31:21.070 --> 00:31:24.860 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
then hope comes in.

00:31:24.860 --> 00:31:27.430 align:middle line:84%
So giving them just
the actual scoring.

00:31:27.430 --> 00:31:30.320 align:middle line:84%
But then the mood scale
analysis goes deeper.

00:31:30.320 --> 00:31:33.540 align:middle line:84%
Because when they respond,
let's say the word "angry"

00:31:33.540 --> 00:31:35.950 align:middle line:84%
comes up on the screen,
and they push zero,

00:31:35.950 --> 00:31:37.950 align:middle line:84%
meaning they're saying
they're not at all angry.

00:31:37.950 --> 00:31:38.215 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I'm not angry.

00:31:38.215 --> 00:31:38.480 align:middle line:90%
I don't have any anger issues.

00:31:38.480 --> 00:31:39.480 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Right, exactly.

00:31:39.480 --> 00:31:43.420 align:middle line:84%
And so later after the chamber
time, and the canopy room,

00:31:43.420 --> 00:31:45.830 align:middle line:84%
and dinner, when we gather
back at the conference table

00:31:45.830 --> 00:31:48.630 align:middle line:84%
to go over the mood scales,
at one point, for example,

00:31:48.630 --> 00:31:51.580 align:middle line:84%
I had the CEO of a billion
dollar company in training.

00:31:51.580 --> 00:31:53.370 align:middle line:90%
And who wants to go first?

00:31:53.370 --> 00:31:54.080 align:middle line:90%
His hand goes up.

00:31:54.080 --> 00:31:57.660 align:middle line:84%
And so I opened his
mood scales and anger

00:31:57.660 --> 00:31:59.500 align:middle line:90%
was at the top of the list.

00:31:59.500 --> 00:32:02.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, the computer
rates the degree

00:32:02.050 --> 00:32:04.476 align:middle line:84%
to which it doubts
a person's answer.

00:32:04.476 --> 00:32:06.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The incoherence
between your answer

00:32:06.350 --> 00:32:08.530 align:middle line:84%
and what your brain waves
are putting out, right?

00:32:08.530 --> 00:32:10.520 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well I would
call it a discrepancy.

00:32:10.520 --> 00:32:13.170 align:middle line:84%
Because I save the
word "coherent"

00:32:13.170 --> 00:32:15.630 align:middle line:84%
for a more mathematical
relationship between the brain

00:32:15.630 --> 00:32:15.900 align:middle line:90%
waves.

00:32:15.900 --> 00:32:16.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, so discrepancy.

00:32:16.630 --> 00:32:17.754 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Yeah, discrepancy.

00:32:17.754 --> 00:32:19.610 align:middle line:84%
And so, as far as
he was concerned,

00:32:19.610 --> 00:32:21.640 align:middle line:84%
consciously, he was
not feeling any anger,

00:32:21.640 --> 00:32:25.000 align:middle line:84%
but the computer
gave him five sigmas.

00:32:25.000 --> 00:32:28.730 align:middle line:84%
Now, one sigma is a 68%
chance his answer is wrong.

00:32:28.730 --> 00:32:30.770 align:middle line:90%
Two sigmas a 95% chance.

00:32:30.770 --> 00:32:31.290 align:middle line:90%
Three--

00:32:31.290 --> 00:32:31.790 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Five is a lot.

00:32:31.790 --> 00:32:32.630 align:middle line:90%
You're way off.

00:32:32.630 --> 00:32:33.338 align:middle line:90%
You're in denial.

00:32:33.338 --> 00:32:36.340 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Yeah, three
sigmas is a 99.7% chance.

00:32:36.340 --> 00:32:38.820 align:middle line:90%
So I know he's an angry man.

00:32:38.820 --> 00:32:41.920 align:middle line:84%
And so I didn't want
him to be-- he's

00:32:41.920 --> 00:32:43.880 align:middle line:90%
the first one and it's day one.

00:32:43.880 --> 00:32:45.510 align:middle line:84%
So I say, well, you
know, sometimes we

00:32:45.510 --> 00:32:47.560 align:middle line:84%
can have emotions
in our unconscious

00:32:47.560 --> 00:32:48.910 align:middle line:90%
that we're not aware of.

00:32:48.910 --> 00:32:52.654 align:middle line:84%
And so the computer detected
anger to quite a strong degree.

00:32:52.654 --> 00:32:54.070 align:middle line:84%
Is there anything
you're aware of?

00:32:54.070 --> 00:32:57.010 align:middle line:90%
And he yelled, no.

00:32:57.010 --> 00:32:59.830 align:middle line:90%
And so it's obvious he's angry.

00:32:59.830 --> 00:33:03.510 align:middle line:84%
So I was trying to
make it easy for him

00:33:03.510 --> 00:33:05.127 align:middle line:84%
to accept the fact
that he was angry.

00:33:05.127 --> 00:33:06.710 align:middle line:84%
And I go, let's see,
how do I do this?

00:33:06.710 --> 00:33:10.250 align:middle line:84%
Well, he's married, so I started
praising women's intuition.

00:33:10.250 --> 00:33:13.050 align:middle line:84%
Saying sometimes women
know things that men don't.

00:33:13.050 --> 00:33:14.915 align:middle line:84%
The stiffening brush
of logical positivism

00:33:14.915 --> 00:33:17.660 align:middle line:90%
pass more lightly over women.

00:33:17.660 --> 00:33:19.810 align:middle line:84%
And I was getting ready
to ask the question,

00:33:19.810 --> 00:33:22.480 align:middle line:84%
well, what would your wife say
if we asked her, are you angry?

00:33:22.480 --> 00:33:24.440 align:middle line:84%
And I hadn't even gotten
to the question yet,

00:33:24.440 --> 00:33:25.360 align:middle line:90%
but he's a bright guy.

00:33:25.360 --> 00:33:26.950 align:middle line:84%
He runs a billion
dollar company.

00:33:26.950 --> 00:33:30.040 align:middle line:84%
And so he loudly and
angrily yells no,

00:33:30.040 --> 00:33:31.665 align:middle line:84%
even before I
asked the question.

00:33:31.665 --> 00:33:33.790 align:middle line:84%
At that point, the other
people in the room kind of

00:33:33.790 --> 00:33:36.170 align:middle line:84%
moved away from
him a little bit.

00:33:36.170 --> 00:33:38.890 align:middle line:84%
And so in that
kind of denial, we

00:33:38.890 --> 00:33:40.537 align:middle line:84%
went quickly through
all of his words.

00:33:40.537 --> 00:33:41.870 align:middle line:90%
Then we'd go to the next person.

00:33:41.870 --> 00:33:43.670 align:middle line:84%
And he didn't own
up to anything.

00:33:43.670 --> 00:33:45.264 align:middle line:84%
So then we go to
the next person.

00:33:45.264 --> 00:33:46.680 align:middle line:84%
And they go through
a word or two.

00:33:46.680 --> 00:33:48.263 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden
we come to a word,

00:33:48.263 --> 00:33:50.280 align:middle line:84%
and they stop, and the
lip trembles a little.

00:33:50.280 --> 00:33:52.130 align:middle line:90%
A tear comes out.

00:33:52.130 --> 00:33:53.960 align:middle line:90%
I go, OK, what's here?

00:33:53.960 --> 00:33:56.290 align:middle line:84%
And then they tell
the story of a trauma

00:33:56.290 --> 00:33:58.710 align:middle line:90%
which is related to this word.

00:33:58.710 --> 00:34:01.270 align:middle line:84%
And so afterwards,
there's like how

00:34:01.270 --> 00:34:02.740 align:middle line:90%
you feel after a spring rain.

00:34:02.740 --> 00:34:05.480 align:middle line:84%
Well, that happened with
everyone in the group.

00:34:05.480 --> 00:34:07.260 align:middle line:90%
So he didn't say anything.

00:34:07.260 --> 00:34:10.090 align:middle line:84%
But the next day he showed up,
still in his three piece suit,

00:34:10.090 --> 00:34:11.000 align:middle line:90%
white shirt a little too tight.

00:34:11.000 --> 00:34:12.409 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Very uncomfortable
for the training.

00:34:12.409 --> 00:34:14.283 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Very uncomfortable
for the training.

00:34:14.283 --> 00:34:16.969 align:middle line:84%
But he opened his suit
coat and he pulled out

00:34:16.969 --> 00:34:18.630 align:middle line:90%
and unfolded a long list.

00:34:18.630 --> 00:34:21.984 align:middle line:84%
And on it he had written all
the people he was angry at.

00:34:21.984 --> 00:34:22.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:34:22.900 --> 00:34:25.989 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: So he had done the
work, at least the beginning.

00:34:25.989 --> 00:34:27.389 align:middle line:90%
Now he knows what, you know.

00:34:27.389 --> 00:34:29.150 align:middle line:84%
So then we say, OK,
now go in the chamber

00:34:29.150 --> 00:34:32.540 align:middle line:84%
and then the forgiveness
process follows.

00:34:32.540 --> 00:34:34.525 align:middle line:84%
And he was able to forgive
all of the people he

00:34:34.525 --> 00:34:35.199 align:middle line:90%
was angry with.

00:34:35.199 --> 00:34:36.650 align:middle line:90%
He was transformed.

00:34:36.650 --> 00:34:37.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I bet.

00:34:37.780 --> 00:34:40.340 align:middle line:84%
What is-- I mean you've
mentioned one of them I'm

00:34:40.340 --> 00:34:43.510 align:middle line:84%
sure is anger-- but of all the
people you've seen through all

00:34:43.510 --> 00:34:48.110 align:middle line:84%
of these years, what are the
top three most denied emotions?

00:34:48.110 --> 00:34:52.170 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well emotions are--
we have three main categories,

00:34:52.170 --> 00:34:58.139 align:middle line:84%
which are sadness and
depression, anger, and fear.

00:34:58.139 --> 00:35:00.430 align:middle line:84%
And pretty much everything
falls into those categories.

00:35:00.430 --> 00:35:02.960 align:middle line:84%
The emotional hierarchy
we use has five elements:

00:35:02.960 --> 00:35:07.610 align:middle line:84%
apathy, sadness, depression,
anger, fear, and joy.

00:35:07.610 --> 00:35:10.450 align:middle line:84%
And so people work
up through these.

00:35:10.450 --> 00:35:13.810 align:middle line:84%
And so people differ in
terms of whether they

00:35:13.810 --> 00:35:15.330 align:middle line:90%
have more problems with sadness.

00:35:15.330 --> 00:35:16.830 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: More
depressed than angry.

00:35:16.830 --> 00:35:18.290 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Although
sometimes words

00:35:18.290 --> 00:35:19.790 align:middle line:84%
that aren't even
in those categories

00:35:19.790 --> 00:35:21.220 align:middle line:84%
will lead to the
big breakthrough.

00:35:21.220 --> 00:35:24.970 align:middle line:84%
Like there was a guy where
the word "shaky" came up.

00:35:24.970 --> 00:35:30.430 align:middle line:84%
And for several days, pre and
post training mood scales,

00:35:30.430 --> 00:35:32.880 align:middle line:90%
I'd ask him about it.

00:35:32.880 --> 00:35:34.620 align:middle line:90%
And he'd go, well this is shaky.

00:35:34.620 --> 00:35:37.110 align:middle line:84%
And as you can
see, I'm not shaky.

00:35:37.110 --> 00:35:42.170 align:middle line:84%
And so after the second-- at
the end of the second day,

00:35:42.170 --> 00:35:44.300 align:middle line:84%
it had come up four
times, denied every time,

00:35:44.300 --> 00:35:45.620 align:middle line:90%
got big signals.

00:35:45.620 --> 00:35:49.325 align:middle line:84%
And I say, you know, shaky
has come up four times.

00:35:49.325 --> 00:35:51.950 align:middle line:84%
And each time you've denied, and
each time you've gotten sigma.

00:35:51.950 --> 00:35:54.965 align:middle line:84%
So I gave you a pass on it,
because you did such good work

00:35:54.965 --> 00:35:55.840 align:middle line:90%
with the other words.

00:35:55.840 --> 00:35:57.310 align:middle line:84%
But I think there's
something here.

00:35:57.310 --> 00:36:01.190 align:middle line:84%
So please, my intuition is it's
somehow locked in your body.

00:36:01.190 --> 00:36:04.810 align:middle line:84%
So go soak in the hot tub
before you come in tomorrow.

00:36:04.810 --> 00:36:06.320 align:middle line:84%
Day three he comes
in, hadn't done

00:36:06.320 --> 00:36:07.742 align:middle line:90%
the soak, shaky's there again.

00:36:07.742 --> 00:36:10.200 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the day when I'm
reading him his mood scales,

00:36:10.200 --> 00:36:11.580 align:middle line:90%
he gets angry.

00:36:11.580 --> 00:36:14.643 align:middle line:84%
And he yells at me, don't
ask me about shaky anymore.

00:36:14.643 --> 00:36:17.160 align:middle line:84%
Well, now I know
there's something there.

00:36:17.160 --> 00:36:18.980 align:middle line:84%
So I wait, we go
through everything.

00:36:18.980 --> 00:36:20.773 align:middle line:84%
And as he's going
out the door, I

00:36:20.773 --> 00:36:23.480 align:middle line:84%
call out Jim-- that was
his name-- how many more

00:36:23.480 --> 00:36:25.990 align:middle line:84%
times would shaky have to
show up in your mood scales

00:36:25.990 --> 00:36:30.150 align:middle line:84%
before I'd have your
permission to ask me about it?

00:36:30.150 --> 00:36:32.120 align:middle line:84%
And he realized that he'd
been a bit of a jerk,

00:36:32.120 --> 00:36:33.340 align:middle line:90%
he didn't have to yell at me.

00:36:33.340 --> 00:36:35.359 align:middle line:90%
And so he goes like that.

00:36:35.359 --> 00:36:36.900 align:middle line:84%
And he goes, well,
what do you think?

00:36:36.900 --> 00:36:39.430 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well I think
that it's somehow related,

00:36:39.430 --> 00:36:40.600 align:middle line:90%
locked in your body.

00:36:40.600 --> 00:36:42.525 align:middle line:84%
So please take that
soak in the hot tub.

00:36:42.525 --> 00:36:43.460 align:middle line:90%
He does that.

00:36:43.460 --> 00:36:45.080 align:middle line:90%
Comes in the next day.

00:36:45.080 --> 00:36:49.330 align:middle line:84%
And then-- oh, actually the
next morning, it was day four.

00:36:49.330 --> 00:36:52.720 align:middle line:84%
He'd gotten into the hot tub
after breakfast and shooting

00:36:52.720 --> 00:36:53.570 align:middle line:90%
baskets.

00:36:53.570 --> 00:36:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And he's all mellow,
like a wet noodle, limp.

00:36:57.500 --> 00:37:00.470 align:middle line:84%
And 45 minutes in,
he opens his eyes.

00:37:00.470 --> 00:37:03.010 align:middle line:84%
He's lying perfectly
still, as far as he knows,

00:37:03.010 --> 00:37:05.790 align:middle line:84%
and the surface of
the water is rippling.

00:37:05.790 --> 00:37:07.590 align:middle line:90%
Now, this is a puzzle to him.

00:37:07.590 --> 00:37:11.280 align:middle line:84%
So he kind of half sits up, and
his right hand under the water

00:37:11.280 --> 00:37:12.064 align:middle line:90%
was doing that.

00:37:12.064 --> 00:37:12.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:37:12.980 --> 00:37:14.390 align:middle line:90%
It was bringing it out.

00:37:14.390 --> 00:37:15.210 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Yes.

00:37:15.210 --> 00:37:18.380 align:middle line:84%
And that released a
long suppressed trauma.

00:37:18.380 --> 00:37:19.241 align:middle line:90%
He was cared for.

00:37:19.241 --> 00:37:20.740 align:middle line:84%
His parents worked
outside the home.

00:37:20.740 --> 00:37:22.330 align:middle line:90%
He had six siblings.

00:37:22.330 --> 00:37:24.380 align:middle line:84%
He was cared for by
a beloved granny.

00:37:24.380 --> 00:37:27.990 align:middle line:84%
I'd heard so much about this--
best granny in the world.

00:37:27.990 --> 00:37:31.020 align:middle line:84%
Well, when he was six,
granny had a stroke.

00:37:31.020 --> 00:37:33.900 align:middle line:84%
And she became,
guess what, shaky.

00:37:33.900 --> 00:37:35.575 align:middle line:90%
She also had personality change.

00:37:35.575 --> 00:37:38.730 align:middle line:84%
She was now cursing,
swearing, biting the children.

00:37:38.730 --> 00:37:40.340 align:middle line:84%
And the last time
he saw his granny,

00:37:40.340 --> 00:37:43.580 align:middle line:84%
she was being literally dragged
out the kitchen door cursing

00:37:43.580 --> 00:37:45.800 align:middle line:90%
and shrieking and shaking.

00:37:45.800 --> 00:37:47.470 align:middle line:84%
And he never saw
his granny again.

00:37:47.470 --> 00:37:50.819 align:middle line:84%
And when he asked his
parents, they would slap him

00:37:50.819 --> 00:37:52.610 align:middle line:84%
and say, shut up and
don't talk about that.

00:37:52.610 --> 00:37:54.550 align:middle line:84%
So he was completely
traumatized.

00:37:54.550 --> 00:37:58.380 align:middle line:84%
And what he did was, he
basically shut down love.

00:37:58.380 --> 00:38:00.860 align:middle line:84%
And so in his forgiveness,
he forgave granny

00:38:00.860 --> 00:38:02.550 align:middle line:84%
for becoming this
mean old hag, he

00:38:02.550 --> 00:38:05.730 align:middle line:84%
forgave his parents for
not counseling him or even

00:38:05.730 --> 00:38:06.930 align:middle line:90%
loving him through it.

00:38:06.930 --> 00:38:10.090 align:middle line:84%
And the big one, he forgive
himself for shutting off love.

00:38:10.090 --> 00:38:13.222 align:middle line:84%
And this totally
transformed him.

00:38:13.222 --> 00:38:14.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's interesting.

00:38:14.430 --> 00:38:17.400 align:middle line:84%
Because as you go through
these, as you say these mood

00:38:17.400 --> 00:38:21.610 align:middle line:84%
evaluations, you'll have your
release around the third day.

00:38:21.610 --> 00:38:23.330 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, oh
good, I got that one.

00:38:23.330 --> 00:38:24.020 align:middle line:90%
That's up.

00:38:24.020 --> 00:38:25.500 align:middle line:84%
And then you find as
you go further into it,

00:38:25.500 --> 00:38:27.620 align:middle line:84%
as they days go on, you
get more of these sigmas

00:38:27.620 --> 00:38:31.160 align:middle line:84%
as more stuff starts
bubbling up from the well

00:38:31.160 --> 00:38:32.920 align:middle line:84%
of the subconscious
mind and trauma.

00:38:32.920 --> 00:38:35.630 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: And you find people
out in your world responding

00:38:35.630 --> 00:38:36.290 align:middle line:90%
to this.

00:38:36.290 --> 00:38:39.470 align:middle line:84%
Recently here in
Sedona we had a couple

00:38:39.470 --> 00:38:43.630 align:middle line:84%
come where the woman had
been born in Singapore.

00:38:43.630 --> 00:38:47.695 align:middle line:84%
Her mother was a twin, and
she had a cousin almost

00:38:47.695 --> 00:38:49.430 align:middle line:90%
her same age, a girl.

00:38:49.430 --> 00:38:51.310 align:middle line:90%
And her mother died.

00:38:51.310 --> 00:38:55.250 align:middle line:84%
And so she was raised with
her cousin by her aunt.

00:38:55.250 --> 00:38:57.720 align:middle line:84%
And the aunt favored
her own daughter.

00:38:57.720 --> 00:39:01.040 align:middle line:84%
And things got worse and
worse, until finally she

00:39:01.040 --> 00:39:03.790 align:middle line:84%
left Singapore and she said,
don't you ever contact me.

00:39:03.790 --> 00:39:06.030 align:middle line:84%
So now she's in the
chamber, and she's

00:39:06.030 --> 00:39:08.900 align:middle line:84%
doing forgiveness on her
aunt-- might be like day four.

00:39:08.900 --> 00:39:12.310 align:middle line:84%
And she hadn't heard from
her aunt in five years.

00:39:12.310 --> 00:39:14.914 align:middle line:84%
And the next day,
although she decided

00:39:14.914 --> 00:39:16.830 align:middle line:84%
she wasn't checking email
during her training,

00:39:16.830 --> 00:39:20.790 align:middle line:84%
she checked email and her aunt
had sent her a letter of love

00:39:20.790 --> 00:39:21.680 align:middle line:90%
and reaching out.

00:39:21.680 --> 00:39:24.527 align:middle line:84%
And they looked at the time
difference between Singapore

00:39:24.527 --> 00:39:26.610 align:middle line:84%
and when she was in the
chamber doing forgiveness,

00:39:26.610 --> 00:39:28.390 align:middle line:84%
there was a three
hour difference.

00:39:28.390 --> 00:39:30.159 align:middle line:84%
Three hours after
she forgave her aunt,

00:39:30.159 --> 00:39:31.200 align:middle line:90%
the aunt wrote the email.

00:39:31.200 --> 00:39:32.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Absolutely,
because we all

00:39:32.910 --> 00:39:35.410 align:middle line:84%
are intertwined in
the field after all.

00:39:35.410 --> 00:39:37.880 align:middle line:84%
And when you have something
that profound happen, of course

00:39:37.880 --> 00:39:39.510 align:middle line:84%
the people that are
intertwined with us

00:39:39.510 --> 00:39:41.482 align:middle line:90%
will feel the effects of that.

00:39:41.482 --> 00:39:42.440 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: And be healed.

00:39:42.440 --> 00:39:43.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And the thing
that's interesting

00:39:43.950 --> 00:39:45.530 align:middle line:84%
about that forgiveness
process, it's

00:39:45.530 --> 00:39:49.690 align:middle line:84%
not like you just go and
say, OK I forgive you.

00:39:49.690 --> 00:39:53.320 align:middle line:84%
No, it's very strident
what has to be done,

00:39:53.320 --> 00:39:55.850 align:middle line:84%
because you're looking
at brain wave numbers.

00:39:55.850 --> 00:39:58.074 align:middle line:84%
The person that's
in the chamber is

00:39:58.074 --> 00:39:59.490 align:middle line:84%
able to look at
their own numbers.

00:39:59.490 --> 00:40:02.010 align:middle line:84%
You go for a couple minutes
of intense concentration,

00:40:02.010 --> 00:40:02.885 align:middle line:90%
emotional engagement.

00:40:02.885 --> 00:40:05.051 align:middle line:84%
And then you open your eyes
and you see how you did.

00:40:05.051 --> 00:40:06.500 align:middle line:84%
And then you go
back down, and you

00:40:06.500 --> 00:40:08.260 align:middle line:84%
do this over a long
period of time.

00:40:08.260 --> 00:40:09.500 align:middle line:90%
You keep doing this.

00:40:09.500 --> 00:40:11.320 align:middle line:90%
And so you can see and chart it.

00:40:11.320 --> 00:40:13.890 align:middle line:84%
And the protocol
requires that you

00:40:13.890 --> 00:40:17.550 align:middle line:84%
reach certain numbers, which
have colors associated.

00:40:17.550 --> 00:40:22.650 align:middle line:84%
And you have to maintain that,
meaning your subconscious'

00:40:22.650 --> 00:40:25.930 align:middle line:84%
release and impact on the brain
is showing itself very clearly

00:40:25.930 --> 00:40:29.270 align:middle line:84%
numerically in terms
of your coherence.

00:40:29.270 --> 00:40:32.080 align:middle line:84%
You can't cheat and say,
oh yeah, I forgave them.

00:40:32.080 --> 00:40:32.650 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:40:32.650 --> 00:40:34.380 align:middle line:84%
And so what I
found-- which is why

00:40:34.380 --> 00:40:38.570 align:middle line:84%
I said that in the open of
this show-- is that really,

00:40:38.570 --> 00:40:41.210 align:middle line:84%
forgiveness we all have a
different definition of it.

00:40:41.210 --> 00:40:42.710 align:middle line:84%
But since it's core
to the training,

00:40:42.710 --> 00:40:45.010 align:middle line:84%
I had to get really clear
on my own definition of it.

00:40:45.010 --> 00:40:47.310 align:middle line:84%
It more has to do with
understanding love

00:40:47.310 --> 00:40:48.050 align:middle line:90%
and acceptance.

00:40:48.050 --> 00:40:49.420 align:middle line:90%
That is what forgiveness is.

00:40:49.420 --> 00:40:51.180 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: To be
effective, forgiveness

00:40:51.180 --> 00:40:52.670 align:middle line:90%
needs to go all the way to love.

00:40:52.670 --> 00:40:54.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it does have to.

00:40:54.020 --> 00:40:54.790 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:40:54.790 --> 00:40:56.310 align:middle line:90%
And then you can see.

00:40:56.310 --> 00:40:57.530 align:middle line:90%
And you don't push people.

00:40:57.530 --> 00:41:00.310 align:middle line:84%
If you can't reach
that goal, then you

00:41:00.310 --> 00:41:03.630 align:middle line:84%
wait, pick it up in the
next session, and try again,

00:41:03.630 --> 00:41:06.810 align:middle line:84%
but don't exhaust yourself
to a point of depression.

00:41:06.810 --> 00:41:08.510 align:middle line:84%
And so, can you talk
a little bit more

00:41:08.510 --> 00:41:09.900 align:middle line:90%
about the forgiveness process?

00:41:09.900 --> 00:41:12.420 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Sure.

00:41:12.420 --> 00:41:14.720 align:middle line:84%
I'll give you a
little background.

00:41:14.720 --> 00:41:18.440 align:middle line:84%
Everybody in America has
heard of the Gallup Poll.

00:41:18.440 --> 00:41:22.110 align:middle line:84%
For a long time before the death
of Sir John Templeton-- a very

00:41:22.110 --> 00:41:25.785 align:middle line:84%
spiritual man and a good friend
of George Gallup-- every couple

00:41:25.785 --> 00:41:28.650 align:middle line:84%
of years Sir John
would get George

00:41:28.650 --> 00:41:30.660 align:middle line:90%
to do a poll on forgiveness.

00:41:30.660 --> 00:41:34.080 align:middle line:84%
Well, one time I had a chance
to read one of the details.

00:41:34.080 --> 00:41:37.730 align:middle line:84%
And in rating the importance
of forgiveness from zero,

00:41:37.730 --> 00:41:41.320 align:middle line:84%
not at all, up to four,
extremely, 80% of Americans

00:41:41.320 --> 00:41:46.200 align:middle line:84%
said they considered forgiveness
extremely important, 80%.

00:41:46.200 --> 00:41:48.960 align:middle line:84%
Then of those who considered
it extremely important,

00:41:48.960 --> 00:41:51.420 align:middle line:84%
George Gallup asked,
well can you do it?

00:41:51.420 --> 00:41:54.050 align:middle line:90%
85% said no.

00:41:54.050 --> 00:41:58.610 align:middle line:84%
Even God's help was not
effective in producing

00:41:58.610 --> 00:42:01.030 align:middle line:84%
what we call effective
forgiveness for most people.

00:42:01.030 --> 00:42:03.460 align:middle line:90%
85% said they could not do it.

00:42:03.460 --> 00:42:05.470 align:middle line:84%
Of the things that
Gallup asked about,

00:42:05.470 --> 00:42:07.540 align:middle line:84%
there was only one thing
that was correlated

00:42:07.540 --> 00:42:08.740 align:middle line:90%
with effective forgiveness.

00:42:08.740 --> 00:42:11.180 align:middle line:90%
And that was meditative prayer.

00:42:11.180 --> 00:42:13.800 align:middle line:84%
Well, when you take
meditative as an adverb

00:42:13.800 --> 00:42:16.720 align:middle line:84%
and put it in front of a
verb, like meditative fishing,

00:42:16.720 --> 00:42:19.850 align:middle line:84%
meditative gardening, meditative
sewing, meditative reading,

00:42:19.850 --> 00:42:22.180 align:middle line:90%
what I see are more alpha waves.

00:42:22.180 --> 00:42:24.740 align:middle line:84%
And so in a sense,
George Gallup has

00:42:24.740 --> 00:42:27.800 align:middle line:84%
revealed that effective
forgiveness requires

00:42:27.800 --> 00:42:28.680 align:middle line:90%
more alpha waves.

00:42:28.680 --> 00:42:31.140 align:middle line:84%
So the way I've incorporated
that into the training

00:42:31.140 --> 00:42:33.797 align:middle line:84%
is, the first thing, you
have to pick a charge.

00:42:33.797 --> 00:42:35.505 align:middle line:84%
You have to pick
somebody, a perpetrator,

00:42:35.505 --> 00:42:38.340 align:middle line:84%
and you want to forgive them,
and then there's a charge.

00:42:38.340 --> 00:42:41.660 align:middle line:84%
You bring in some high beings
as your observers or judges.

00:42:41.660 --> 00:42:43.494 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: They can be
your guides, or angels.

00:42:43.494 --> 00:42:45.201 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Your guides,
angels, absolutely.

00:42:45.201 --> 00:42:47.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Whoever you wish
A team, a supportive team.

00:42:47.570 --> 00:42:49.850 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: But it can't
be your favorite uncle.

00:42:49.850 --> 00:42:52.070 align:middle line:90%
They need to be flawless beings.

00:42:52.070 --> 00:42:55.280 align:middle line:84%
And so then the first thing,
when you make the charge,

00:42:55.280 --> 00:42:56.740 align:middle line:90%
you have to feel the pain.

00:42:56.740 --> 00:43:00.070 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you can't feel the
pain because it's blocked--

00:43:00.070 --> 00:43:02.820 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes people are so
armored, the pain is so great,

00:43:02.820 --> 00:43:05.620 align:middle line:84%
they can't feel it--
their alpha won't drop.

00:43:05.620 --> 00:43:07.320 align:middle line:84%
If you can feel the
pain, your alpha

00:43:07.320 --> 00:43:10.690 align:middle line:84%
will drop, which then causes the
color of the numerical scores

00:43:10.690 --> 00:43:11.860 align:middle line:90%
to turn white.

00:43:11.860 --> 00:43:14.160 align:middle line:84%
You need a majority
of scores to be white.

00:43:14.160 --> 00:43:16.960 align:middle line:84%
If you get that,
only then can you

00:43:16.960 --> 00:43:19.860 align:middle line:84%
advance to the next step,
which is doing the forgiveness.

00:43:19.860 --> 00:43:22.210 align:middle line:84%
Walk in the person's
shoes, realize

00:43:22.210 --> 00:43:25.070 align:middle line:84%
that they weren't
playing with a full deck.

00:43:25.070 --> 00:43:27.400 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it is, telling
them you love them.

00:43:27.400 --> 00:43:30.150 align:middle line:84%
Understanding the difficulties
they had in their life.

00:43:30.150 --> 00:43:31.077 align:middle line:90%
And hugging them.

00:43:31.077 --> 00:43:32.160 align:middle line:90%
And saying, I forgive you.

00:43:32.160 --> 00:43:33.490 align:middle line:90%
Whatever it is that works.

00:43:33.490 --> 00:43:35.810 align:middle line:84%
And if your alpha's
going up, your scores

00:43:35.810 --> 00:43:38.590 align:middle line:84%
are going to be in
blues or greens.

00:43:38.590 --> 00:43:41.750 align:middle line:84%
And so as long as that's
working, you keep doing it.

00:43:41.750 --> 00:43:43.760 align:middle line:90%
You don't stop part way through.

00:43:43.760 --> 00:43:46.530 align:middle line:84%
Only when you run out of
steam, and the alpha drops,

00:43:46.530 --> 00:43:48.990 align:middle line:84%
and the scores turn white again
do you turn to your judges

00:43:48.990 --> 00:43:52.460 align:middle line:84%
and say, have I done
all I can do for now?

00:43:52.460 --> 00:43:55.960 align:middle line:84%
And if the judges are unanimous,
then you rest, celebrate,

00:43:55.960 --> 00:43:57.670 align:middle line:84%
or you go onto the
next forgiveness.

00:43:57.670 --> 00:44:00.880 align:middle line:84%
If the judges, even one of
them, say no, you go back,

00:44:00.880 --> 00:44:02.930 align:middle line:84%
feel the pain again,
and you start over.

00:44:02.930 --> 00:44:05.080 align:middle line:84%
That way you're
always maximizing

00:44:05.080 --> 00:44:06.840 align:middle line:84%
the amount of
forgiveness you can do.

00:44:06.840 --> 00:44:09.860 align:middle line:84%
One time in Canada, where we
have a First Nation scholarship

00:44:09.860 --> 00:44:12.050 align:middle line:84%
program for Canadian
aboriginals,

00:44:12.050 --> 00:44:13.930 align:middle line:84%
there was a First
Nations man who

00:44:13.930 --> 00:44:17.290 align:middle line:84%
was sent back five
times by his judges

00:44:17.290 --> 00:44:19.120 align:middle line:90%
on forgiving a certain person.

00:44:19.120 --> 00:44:22.250 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of sexual abuse,
and alcoholism, and drugs,

00:44:22.250 --> 00:44:26.460 align:middle line:84%
and physical abuse in the
aboriginal community in Canada.

00:44:26.460 --> 00:44:30.800 align:middle line:84%
And on the fifth time
when he was sent back,

00:44:30.800 --> 00:44:33.320 align:middle line:84%
the judges accepted
and said, OK,

00:44:33.320 --> 00:44:34.870 align:middle line:90%
that's all you can do for today.

00:44:34.870 --> 00:44:36.880 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well what
did you do different?

00:44:36.880 --> 00:44:41.480 align:middle line:84%
And he went, well, I
went all the way to love.

00:44:41.480 --> 00:44:42.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Interesting.

00:44:42.850 --> 00:44:45.650 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about how
that displays itself.

00:44:45.650 --> 00:44:49.590 align:middle line:84%
Once you're able-- because these
traumas-- most of these traumas

00:44:49.590 --> 00:44:51.060 align:middle line:84%
have to do with
other human beings

00:44:51.060 --> 00:44:52.020 align:middle line:90%
and events that have happened.

00:44:52.020 --> 00:44:54.610 align:middle line:84%
Some of them are random, like
a car accident or something

00:44:54.610 --> 00:44:55.819 align:middle line:90%
where it doesn't necessarily.

00:44:55.819 --> 00:44:56.734 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Or a disease.

00:44:56.734 --> 00:44:59.320 align:middle line:84%
You can forgive the this
virus, or the that virus, polio

00:44:59.320 --> 00:45:00.420 align:middle line:90%
or whatever.

00:45:00.420 --> 00:45:01.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:45:01.190 --> 00:45:04.140 align:middle line:84%
And so once you go through
that, and once this trauma

00:45:04.140 --> 00:45:07.410 align:middle line:84%
has been felt, you've
taken it back up as high

00:45:07.410 --> 00:45:10.150 align:middle line:84%
as you can toward a
state of love, then

00:45:10.150 --> 00:45:12.750 align:middle line:84%
what happens in
the brain itself?

00:45:12.750 --> 00:45:16.257 align:middle line:84%
What's going on there that
puts us into this high state?

00:45:16.257 --> 00:45:17.840 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well, there's
a number things

00:45:17.840 --> 00:45:20.580 align:middle line:84%
going on cortically as
well as subcortically.

00:45:20.580 --> 00:45:22.720 align:middle line:84%
For example, we've
worked with soldiers

00:45:22.720 --> 00:45:25.140 align:middle line:84%
who had post-traumatic
stress disorder.

00:45:25.140 --> 00:45:29.090 align:middle line:84%
And we know from other
studies that in these states--

00:45:29.090 --> 00:45:33.670 align:middle line:84%
for example, there's excessive
activity in the amygdala which

00:45:33.670 --> 00:45:36.190 align:middle line:90%
is part of the limbic system.

00:45:36.190 --> 00:45:38.660 align:middle line:90%
And so excess firing.

00:45:38.660 --> 00:45:41.720 align:middle line:84%
People are then angry,
explosively and so on.

00:45:41.720 --> 00:45:44.470 align:middle line:84%
And so working with
the alpha actually

00:45:44.470 --> 00:45:48.200 align:middle line:84%
helps to calm down and
reduce excess activity

00:45:48.200 --> 00:45:49.670 align:middle line:90%
in the limbic system.

00:45:49.670 --> 00:45:52.400 align:middle line:84%
So things are happening not just
at the surface of the brain,

00:45:52.400 --> 00:45:55.010 align:middle line:90%
but also in the depths.

00:45:55.010 --> 00:46:00.110 align:middle line:84%
And so there's a statement that
says "insults are never given,

00:46:00.110 --> 00:46:01.710 align:middle line:90%
they're only received."

00:46:01.710 --> 00:46:04.570 align:middle line:84%
And so if somebody says,
la la la, and you go,

00:46:04.570 --> 00:46:07.740 align:middle line:84%
what a lovely tone of
voice you have used.

00:46:07.740 --> 00:46:09.940 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know you
could be a singer.

00:46:09.940 --> 00:46:11.790 align:middle line:84%
So whatever was
the content-- which

00:46:11.790 --> 00:46:14.460 align:middle line:84%
they might have intended
to be an insult-- it just

00:46:14.460 --> 00:46:17.290 align:middle line:84%
completely didn't land on you
because you didn't receive it

00:46:17.290 --> 00:46:18.620 align:middle line:90%
in that way.

00:46:18.620 --> 00:46:20.410 align:middle line:84%
Marshall Thurber
says, "Communication

00:46:20.410 --> 00:46:21.610 align:middle line:90%
is what's received."

00:46:21.610 --> 00:46:25.110 align:middle line:84%
And with alpha, when
you're in this state,

00:46:25.110 --> 00:46:28.860 align:middle line:84%
you are almost
invulnerable to negativity.

00:46:28.860 --> 00:46:32.850 align:middle line:84%
You can handle a much wider
range of aberrant behavior.

00:46:32.850 --> 00:46:36.850 align:middle line:84%
This is one of the reasons why
the statistically strongest

00:46:36.850 --> 00:46:39.090 align:middle line:84%
effect of the alpha
one training is

00:46:39.090 --> 00:46:40.930 align:middle line:90%
improvement in relationships.

00:46:40.930 --> 00:46:42.700 align:middle line:84%
Now, it doesn't
mean that you choose

00:46:42.700 --> 00:46:43.865 align:middle line:90%
to have negative relations.

00:46:43.865 --> 00:46:47.660 align:middle line:84%
You may in fact choose to have
only more positive relations.

00:46:47.660 --> 00:46:49.780 align:middle line:84%
But if you find
yourself in a situation

00:46:49.780 --> 00:46:52.195 align:middle line:84%
where people are dumping
negativity on you

00:46:52.195 --> 00:46:56.170 align:middle line:84%
or making stressful demands,
you can be equanimous about it.

00:46:56.170 --> 00:46:57.090 align:middle line:90%
You can be peaceful.

00:46:57.090 --> 00:46:57.673 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:46:57.673 --> 00:46:59.990 align:middle line:84%
And what I found
on a personal level

00:46:59.990 --> 00:47:03.420 align:middle line:84%
with this is, after the training
and the next couple months--

00:47:03.420 --> 00:47:05.730 align:middle line:84%
it had been a couple
months-- that followed,

00:47:05.730 --> 00:47:12.700 align:middle line:84%
was that I was acknowledging
the kind of relationship

00:47:12.700 --> 00:47:15.920 align:middle line:90%
that I actually chose to be in.

00:47:15.920 --> 00:47:20.650 align:middle line:84%
I mean, my choices changed very
radically and very rapidly.

00:47:20.650 --> 00:47:21.950 align:middle line:90%
The choices changed.

00:47:21.950 --> 00:47:24.210 align:middle line:84%
And not only did
the choices change,

00:47:24.210 --> 00:47:26.220 align:middle line:90%
but the resonance changed.

00:47:26.220 --> 00:47:29.400 align:middle line:84%
People on a different
field-- that

00:47:29.400 --> 00:47:32.800 align:middle line:84%
are more in resonance
with me on that level

00:47:32.800 --> 00:47:34.904 align:middle line:90%
started coming into my life.

00:47:34.904 --> 00:47:36.570 align:middle line:84%
Or I started being
in contact with them,

00:47:36.570 --> 00:47:38.860 align:middle line:84%
whether it's work,
friendship, or whatnot.

00:47:38.860 --> 00:47:41.870 align:middle line:84%
And so the resonance
changed when

00:47:41.870 --> 00:47:46.050 align:middle line:84%
it comes to relationship
completely, actually.

00:47:46.050 --> 00:47:47.620 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it really was amazing.

00:47:47.620 --> 00:47:51.590 align:middle line:84%
I found the whole process--
as I said, it's work.

00:47:51.590 --> 00:47:52.630 align:middle line:90%
You have to work at it.

00:47:52.630 --> 00:47:53.630 align:middle line:90%
You have to be diligent.

00:47:53.630 --> 00:47:55.520 align:middle line:84%
You can't be lazy, or you
don't get the results.

00:47:55.520 --> 00:47:57.060 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: The machine
won't do it to you.

00:47:57.060 --> 00:47:58.393 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It won't do it to you.

00:47:58.393 --> 00:48:01.010 align:middle line:90%
And you can't fool the system.

00:48:01.010 --> 00:48:03.310 align:middle line:84%
You can't kind of BS
your way out of it.

00:48:03.310 --> 00:48:04.930 align:middle line:90%
Oh no, I didn't feel like that.

00:48:04.930 --> 00:48:09.516 align:middle line:84%
And so I really like that
degree of scientific scrutiny

00:48:09.516 --> 00:48:11.890 align:middle line:84%
that was taking place, because
you had to get down in it,

00:48:11.890 --> 00:48:13.550 align:middle line:90%
and then you had to release it.

00:48:13.550 --> 00:48:18.010 align:middle line:84%
And so yes, relationships
definitely very beautifully

00:48:18.010 --> 00:48:18.850 align:middle line:90%
impacted by it.

00:48:18.850 --> 00:48:22.310 align:middle line:84%
I found, on a personal level,
as did the people in our group,

00:48:22.310 --> 00:48:24.060 align:middle line:84%
because I know we had
one man in our group

00:48:24.060 --> 00:48:28.060 align:middle line:84%
who was a young man who's
very successful in his chosen

00:48:28.060 --> 00:48:28.990 align:middle line:90%
profession.

00:48:28.990 --> 00:48:31.830 align:middle line:84%
And he just kept saying,
no, I don't feel like that.

00:48:31.830 --> 00:48:33.871 align:middle line:84%
Must be something wrong
with your technology.

00:48:33.871 --> 00:48:34.620 align:middle line:90%
I don't feel like.

00:48:34.620 --> 00:48:37.070 align:middle line:84%
He kept every day
saying something was

00:48:37.070 --> 00:48:39.080 align:middle line:84%
wrong with your
technology, and then

00:48:39.080 --> 00:48:41.340 align:middle line:84%
had a massive
emotional breakthrough

00:48:41.340 --> 00:48:44.980 align:middle line:84%
in the end of something so
deeply hidden from himself

00:48:44.980 --> 00:48:47.540 align:middle line:84%
that he ended up at
the end of it saying--

00:48:47.540 --> 00:48:49.770 align:middle line:84%
because he's a
conscious young man.

00:48:49.770 --> 00:48:53.100 align:middle line:84%
He goes to every kind of
workshop, every seminar.

00:48:53.100 --> 00:48:55.740 align:middle line:84%
He knew practically half
the people I've interviewed,

00:48:55.740 --> 00:48:58.330 align:middle line:84%
he's either read their
book or attended.

00:48:58.330 --> 00:49:00.950 align:middle line:84%
But it wasn't getting to
that point, that little place

00:49:00.950 --> 00:49:03.690 align:middle line:90%
deep inside that was very hurt.

00:49:03.690 --> 00:49:06.450 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, I'm just
validating that what you do

00:49:06.450 --> 00:49:11.110 align:middle line:84%
has such depth, and such
beauty, and such effectiveness.

00:49:11.110 --> 00:49:13.554 align:middle line:90%
So I just had to share that.

00:49:13.554 --> 00:49:14.720 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Thank you for that.

00:49:14.720 --> 00:49:15.969 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You're most welcome.

00:49:15.969 --> 00:49:19.400 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about what people
can do if they can't make it

00:49:19.400 --> 00:49:22.480 align:middle line:84%
to-- if they can't
do this training,

00:49:22.480 --> 00:49:25.670 align:middle line:84%
let's talk about what we can do
for ourselves, because anybody

00:49:25.670 --> 00:49:28.300 align:middle line:84%
watching this, besides not
eating onions, and garlic,

00:49:28.300 --> 00:49:30.550 align:middle line:84%
and a big meal at
night, what can we

00:49:30.550 --> 00:49:34.200 align:middle line:84%
do for ourselves to
facilitate our own forgiveness

00:49:34.200 --> 00:49:37.585 align:middle line:84%
process on somewhat
of an objective scale?

00:49:37.585 --> 00:49:39.960 align:middle line:84%
Because granted, we're not
going to have machines saying,

00:49:39.960 --> 00:49:41.530 align:middle line:90%
you're lying to yourself here.

00:49:41.530 --> 00:49:42.439 align:middle line:90%
How can we do this?

00:49:42.439 --> 00:49:43.980 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: Well, one
simple thing would

00:49:43.980 --> 00:49:47.620 align:middle line:84%
be to buy a copy of my book,
"The Art of Smart Thinking,"

00:49:47.620 --> 00:49:50.650 align:middle line:84%
which you can get through
Amazon, "The Art of Smart

00:49:50.650 --> 00:49:51.490 align:middle line:90%
Thinking."

00:49:51.490 --> 00:49:53.940 align:middle line:84%
And in there,
among other things,

00:49:53.940 --> 00:49:56.870 align:middle line:84%
the forgiveness
process is detailed.

00:49:56.870 --> 00:49:58.780 align:middle line:84%
And so people can
read through that.

00:49:58.780 --> 00:50:02.010 align:middle line:84%
Now of course, the
process is more effective

00:50:02.010 --> 00:50:05.650 align:middle line:84%
and more powerful when you
interact with the technology.

00:50:05.650 --> 00:50:06.490 align:middle line:90%
But for example--

00:50:06.490 --> 00:50:07.320 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's much
faster, of course.

00:50:07.320 --> 00:50:08.390 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Much faster.

00:50:08.390 --> 00:50:12.523 align:middle line:84%
But for example, in Canada one
of the aboriginals who trained

00:50:12.523 --> 00:50:17.480 align:middle line:90%
was a-- he's a priest.

00:50:17.480 --> 00:50:21.980 align:middle line:84%
As a small boy, he was
picked up every Saturday

00:50:21.980 --> 00:50:25.260 align:middle line:84%
by the Indian Agent,
taken off the reserve,

00:50:25.260 --> 00:50:26.470 align:middle line:90%
and sexually abused.

00:50:26.470 --> 00:50:29.010 align:middle line:90%
So he had a lot of trauma.

00:50:29.010 --> 00:50:32.290 align:middle line:84%
However now as a priest, he
has a very, very deep interest

00:50:32.290 --> 00:50:33.790 align:middle line:90%
in teaching forgiveness.

00:50:33.790 --> 00:50:37.120 align:middle line:84%
And so he has used the
Biocybernaut forgiveness

00:50:37.120 --> 00:50:37.620 align:middle line:90%
method.

00:50:37.620 --> 00:50:41.560 align:middle line:84%
And what started was he asked
me if he could use it just

00:50:41.560 --> 00:50:43.840 align:middle line:84%
to talk about it,
and then do whatever

00:50:43.840 --> 00:50:46.610 align:middle line:84%
he could to help people
to go through the steps

00:50:46.610 --> 00:50:48.400 align:middle line:90%
without the feedback.

00:50:48.400 --> 00:50:54.390 align:middle line:84%
And so his parish
agreed to let him

00:50:54.390 --> 00:50:59.390 align:middle line:84%
have a class in the church
on a weekday evening.

00:50:59.390 --> 00:51:02.365 align:middle line:84%
Well pretty quickly,
the church was full.

00:51:02.365 --> 00:51:05.550 align:middle line:84%
And so they had to let him
have another night in the week

00:51:05.550 --> 00:51:06.210 align:middle line:90%
to do that.

00:51:06.210 --> 00:51:11.020 align:middle line:84%
So it's possible to read this,
and to incorporate it, and use

00:51:11.020 --> 00:51:13.920 align:middle line:84%
it to advance your
own forgiveness.

00:51:13.920 --> 00:51:16.470 align:middle line:84%
Again, it's not as powerful as
doing it with the technology,

00:51:16.470 --> 00:51:19.270 align:middle line:84%
but it is something
that you can do.

00:51:19.270 --> 00:51:21.880 align:middle line:84%
Also in the book are
a number of stories

00:51:21.880 --> 00:51:24.770 align:middle line:84%
about people's work,
the transformations,

00:51:24.770 --> 00:51:26.400 align:middle line:84%
the kind of traumas
they've dealt with.

00:51:26.400 --> 00:51:27.910 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times
that can speak

00:51:27.910 --> 00:51:29.770 align:middle line:90%
to people in a very deep way.

00:51:29.770 --> 00:51:31.770 align:middle line:84%
So one of the things it
does is gives them hope,

00:51:31.770 --> 00:51:33.490 align:middle line:84%
because sometimes
people say, well,

00:51:33.490 --> 00:51:36.300 align:middle line:84%
the thing that happened to
me is just unforgivable.

00:51:36.300 --> 00:51:38.850 align:middle line:84%
And then they read a
story about somebody

00:51:38.850 --> 00:51:41.649 align:middle line:84%
who had something far
worse happen to them,

00:51:41.649 --> 00:51:43.190 align:middle line:84%
and how they were
able to forgive it.

00:51:43.190 --> 00:51:46.664 align:middle line:84%
And then it motivates people
to begin to open their hearts.

00:51:46.664 --> 00:51:48.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it
would seem to me,

00:51:48.080 --> 00:51:52.520 align:middle line:84%
as long as you have
the ability to focus,

00:51:52.520 --> 00:51:54.120 align:middle line:90%
to hold a clear thought.

00:51:54.120 --> 00:51:56.260 align:middle line:84%
And you have the
dedicated time where

00:51:56.260 --> 00:51:58.820 align:middle line:84%
you're choosing to
set aside the time,

00:51:58.820 --> 00:52:01.700 align:middle line:84%
because it's not easy
to go through this.

00:52:01.700 --> 00:52:03.306 align:middle line:90%
Say, I am ready to take this on.

00:52:03.306 --> 00:52:04.180 align:middle line:90%
You have to be ready.

00:52:04.180 --> 00:52:07.230 align:middle line:84%
If you're not ready, it's
not going to happen, right?

00:52:07.230 --> 00:52:08.410 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Mm-hmm.

00:52:08.410 --> 00:52:11.500 align:middle line:84%
And methods differ in
their effectiveness.

00:52:11.500 --> 00:52:15.850 align:middle line:84%
Like Zen, which is a very
powerful meditation technique,

00:52:15.850 --> 00:52:18.680 align:middle line:84%
minimum 21 years
to get to the point

00:52:18.680 --> 00:52:21.635 align:middle line:84%
where the Zen masters rate
the students as advanced.

00:52:21.635 --> 00:52:25.000 align:middle line:84%
And in some cases it
takes up to 40 years,

00:52:25.000 --> 00:52:26.970 align:middle line:90%
21 to 40 years of Zen practice.

00:52:26.970 --> 00:52:29.920 align:middle line:84%
Now besides meditation,
which I endorse,

00:52:29.920 --> 00:52:32.930 align:middle line:84%
meditation and
prayer can be very

00:52:32.930 --> 00:52:36.230 align:middle line:84%
powerful, it's helpful
to combine them

00:52:36.230 --> 00:52:39.580 align:middle line:84%
with breathing exercises,
where you do slow,

00:52:39.580 --> 00:52:42.810 align:middle line:84%
deep breathing for
a while before you

00:52:42.810 --> 00:52:45.600 align:middle line:84%
start your meditation
or your prayer.

00:52:45.600 --> 00:52:48.370 align:middle line:84%
And so you sit down, and
you take a few deep breaths.

00:52:48.370 --> 00:52:51.499 align:middle line:84%
And then you breathe in,
as slowly as you can, hold.

00:52:51.499 --> 00:52:53.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Like for 8 counts,
or 10 counts, or whatever.

00:52:53.790 --> 00:52:55.380 align:middle line:90%
>>HARDT: Yeah, 8, 10, whatever.

00:52:55.380 --> 00:52:57.650 align:middle line:90%
Inhale, hold, exhale.

00:52:57.650 --> 00:53:00.710 align:middle line:84%
And you do like
a dozen of those.

00:53:00.710 --> 00:53:03.680 align:middle line:84%
And then you go into the
meditation and the prayer.

00:53:03.680 --> 00:53:06.360 align:middle line:84%
And in my work,
I've demonstrated

00:53:06.360 --> 00:53:10.430 align:middle line:84%
that doing a slow breathing
before the meditation

00:53:10.430 --> 00:53:14.444 align:middle line:84%
will make there be more alpha
than if you just sit down

00:53:14.444 --> 00:53:15.360 align:middle line:90%
and start to meditate.

00:53:15.360 --> 00:53:16.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
it seems like that

00:53:16.160 --> 00:53:18.310 align:middle line:84%
would have a very direct
impact on the nervous system,

00:53:18.310 --> 00:53:19.820 align:middle line:84%
calming both the
mind and the body.

00:53:19.820 --> 00:53:24.760 align:middle line:84%
So it's a little easier
starting place for a person.

00:53:24.760 --> 00:53:25.350 align:middle line:90%
Excellent.

00:53:25.350 --> 00:53:28.000 align:middle line:84%
>>HARDT: And I can give you
a little of the biochemistry.

00:53:28.000 --> 00:53:30.390 align:middle line:84%
When you do slow,
deep breathing--

00:53:30.390 --> 00:53:33.740 align:middle line:84%
and I'm talking about
really, and then hold--

00:53:33.740 --> 00:53:36.647 align:middle line:84%
and when you exhale, most
people exchange about 20%

00:53:36.647 --> 00:53:38.480 align:middle line:84%
and the air in their
lungs with each breath.

00:53:38.480 --> 00:53:41.200 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of
stale air in the lungs.

00:53:41.200 --> 00:53:44.600 align:middle line:84%
So in this breathing
exercise, when the exhale, you

00:53:44.600 --> 00:53:46.980 align:middle line:84%
pull in your tummy, and
you collapse your chest,

00:53:46.980 --> 00:53:50.540 align:middle line:84%
